npm init -y
npm install express mysql2 cors


Frontend

HTML for structure

CSS for styling & responsiveness

JavaScript (fetch) for API calls



Backend

Node.js + Express

REST APIs (POST, GET, PUT, DELETE)

Business logic handled in server



Database

MySQL

Unique constraint on USN to avoid duplicates

Features

Add, update, delete students

Filter top performers

Responsive UI

Data integrity enforced at DB level

Flow
Browser → JavaScript → Express API → MySQL → JSON → UI